    jTextArea1.setText("╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║ ▪ Each line may contain one command.                                  ║\n║ ▪ Turtle logo is not case sensitive.                                  ║\n║ ▪ Spacing between tokens is optional (fd10 is equivalent to fd 10).   ║\n║ ▪ Values preceded by a # indicate a hexadecimal integer.              ║\n║ ▪ Rogue/malformed commands result in undefined behavior.              ║\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n┌───────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│Command    │ Description of command                                    │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│//         │ Lines that start with // are treated as a comment.        │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│fd 40.5    │ Moves turtle forward 40.5 units.                          │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│bk 17.6    │ Moves turtle backward 17.6 units.                         │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│rt 7.5     │ Turns turtle 7.5° to its right.                           │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│lt 23.1    │ Turns turtle 23.1° to its left.                           │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│pu         │ Pen up (turtle will not leave a path when moving).        │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│pd         │ Pen down (turtle will leave a path when moving).          │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│pc #FF00FF │ Changes the pen color to the indicated RGB value.         │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│hm         │ Turtle portals to the center of the screen, facing north. │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│re 15      │ Turtle will repeat commands after this line and up until  │\n│           │ the next matching \"er\" 15 times.                          │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│er         │ Marks the end of the nearest repeat command.  Leaving off │\n│           │ an \"er\" results in undefined behavior.                    │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│_a := 5.1  │ Assigns the global variable _a to 5.1.  Global variables  │\n│           │ start with an underscore and _a through _z are available  │\n│           │ and initialized to 0.0.  However, _x, _y, and _z          │\n│           │ automatically change to reflect the turtle's current      │\n│           │ (x, y) and angle values.                                  │\n│           │                                                           │\n│           │ Global variables may be used with the preceding commands. │\n│           │ For example:   fd _a   (or)   rt _b   (or)   re _c        │\n│           │                                                           │\n│           │ The operators that modify variables are +=, -=, *= and /= │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│de @a      │ Marks the beginning of the definition of a procedure      │\n│           │ named @a.  Procedure names @a through @z are available.   │\n│           │ Procedures cannot be nested within other procedures.      │\n│           │ Procedures must be defined before they are called.        │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ed         │ Marks the end of the definition of a procedure.  Leaving  │\n│           │ off an \"ed\" results in undefined behavior.                │\n├───────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│do @a      │ Calls the procedure named @a and returns when the         │\n│           │ procedure completes.                                      │\n└───────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘");
